DIGEST
SB 321 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Kleinpeter
Present law allows for the posting of electronic bonds. Proposed law retains present law.
Proposed law requires any parish implementing the use of electronic bonds to also allow the
use of in-person bonds.
Proposed law authorizes the sheriff to establish additional requirements for approval of
electronic bonds in a parish.
Proposed law requires electronic bond providers to maintain a registry of agents approved
by the sheriff to execute electronic bonds in the parish. Further provides that the bond
provider shall verify the agent seeking the bond is on the registry.
Proposed law provides procedures for the issuance of electronic bonds. Further provides for
